FAQ: Installation
=================

How do I get started?
---------------------

    #. `Download the code`_.
    #. Install Bombardier Server (read the :ref:`installation guide <intro-install>`).
    #. Walk through the :ref:`tutorial <intro-tutorial01>`.
    #. Check out the rest of the :ref:`documentation <index>`, and `ask questions`_ if you
       run into trouble.

.. _`Download the code`: https://launchpad.net/bombardier/+download
.. _ask questions: https://answers.launchpad.net/bombardier

What are Bombardier's prerequisites?
------------------------------------

Bombardier Server requires Python_ 2.5 or 2.6. There is also a Bombardier Client, which can run on any version of Python from 2.4 through 2.6.

In addition, Bombardier Server requires several Python libraries to be installed as a pre-requisite. These libraries all come native on Ubuntu Hardy, which is the target platform for the Bombardier Server system. If you are using another distribution of Linux, you may have to download and build these libraries on your own. The libraries required are:

	* `PyCrypto 2.0.1`_
	* `PExpect 2.1`_
	* `PyYaml 3.08`_
	* `Syck for Python 0.61`_
	* `Django 1.0.4 Python web server`_
	* `Pyro 3.9.1`_
	
.. _PyCrypto 2.0.1: http://www.amk.ca/python/code/crypto.html
.. _PExpect 2.1: http://www.noah.org/wiki/Pexpect
.. _PyYaml 3.08: http://pyyaml.org/
.. _Syck for Python 0.61: http://freshmeat.net/projects/syck/
.. _Django 1.0.4 Python web server: http://www.djangoproject.com/
.. _Pyro 3.9.1: http://pyro.sourceforge.net/


